    • keySet

      public Set<String> keySet()
      Returns a Set view of the keys contained in this JSON object. The set is backed by the JSON object, so changes to the JSON object are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. If the JSON object is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined.
      Returns:
      a set view of the keys contained in this JSON object

    • values

      public Collection<JsonElement> values()
      Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this JSON object. The collection is backed by the JSON object, so changes to the JSON object are reflected in the collection, and vice-versa. If the JSON object is modified while an iteration over the collection is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined.
      Returns:
      a collection view of the values contained in this JSON object
